Forty-nine people died in two separate bus  accidents in the Eastern Transvaal province of South Africa Thursday, police  said.
At Lothair, 36 foresty workers were killed when their bus lost control and  plunged into a dam. Police said they believed most of the victims had drowned.
In a later accident at the steel town of Middelburg, 13 people were killed  when a minibus was flung into a truck after being involved in a collision.
Twelve people travelling in the minibus were killed, as was the driver of  a car involved in the collision.
